# Local AI add-ons

- Privacy-first: no cloud transcription, no telemetry, no background uploads. HF token is user-owned only; store in `safeStorage`, never in logs, metadata, transcripts, or progress events. Setup validation prefers `--token-stdin` (not `HF_TOKEN` in the child process environment).
- Catalog-driven pins live in `src/ai-addon-state.js` — do not hard-code URLs, checksums, or runtime names in renderer logic.
- Diarization: auto after transcription when ready; prefer guided transcription (pyannote → padded windows → transcribe). macOS diarization is Apple Silicon MPS-only.
- Summaries: always user-triggered; explicit setup only; HTTPS + explicit host allowlist (`DOWNLOAD_REDIRECT_HOSTS` in `src/ai-addon/download-helpers.js` — maintain when HF/Xet CDNs rotate; no `*.hf.co` wildcards); ZIP/tar.gz runtime extraction uses `src/ai-addon-archive-helpers.js` plus worker threads; verify SHA-256 after download. HF-hosted summary models prefer bundled Python `hf_xet` and still pin SHA-256.
- Serialize GPU-heavy diarization and summary runs through the main-process compute queue.
- Meeting AI metadata: only `diarization` and `summary`; sidecars under recordings; concise sanitized strings.
- **Cache separation:** diarization HF cache under `userData/ai-addons/models/diarization`; Whisper cache is separate — see `transcription-model-cache.mdc` for guided transcription env vars.
- Stale summaries: honor `sourceTranscriptHash` when transcript changes.
- Catalog/runtime changes: update `src/ai-addon-state.js`, `src/ai-addon-setup.js` if needed, `docs/development/LOCAL_AI_MODEL_CATALOG.md`, and `tests/js/ai-addon-*.test.js`.
- Manual QA: `tests/manual/local-ai-addons-checklist.md`.
